This is why I was so specific with that =E2=80=9C27 year=E2=80=9D reference=
 above; Apple=E2=80=99s 2007 launch of the iPhone marked the end of both Mi=
crosoft and Intel=E2=80=99s dominance, and for the same reason. The shift t=
o efficiency as the top priority meant that you needed to rewrite everythin=
g ; that, by extension, meant that Microsoft=E2=80=99s API and Intel=E2=80=
=99s x86 instruction set were no longer moats but millstones. On the operat=
ing side Apple stripped macOS to the bones and rebuilt it for efficiency; t=
hat became iOS, and the new foundation for apps; on the processor side Appl=
e used processors based on the ARM instruction set, which was RISC from the=
