he rewriting wasn=E2=80=99t happening by choice, but by necessity.

This leads, as I remarked to Fadell in that interview, to a rather sympathe=
tic interpretation of Microsoft and Intel=E2=80=99s failure to capture the =
mobile market; neither company had a chance. They were too invested in the =
dominant paradigm at the time, and thus unable to start from scratch; by th=
e time they realized their mistake, Apple, Android, and ARM had already won=
