d doomed Intel. For the first seven years of the iPhone both companies refu=
sed to accept their failure, and tried desperately to leverage what they vi=
ewed as their unassailable advantages: Microsoft declined to put its produc=
tivity applications on iOS or Android, trying to get customers to adopt Win=
dows Mobile, while Intel tried to bring its manufacturing prowess to bear t=
o build processors that were sufficiently efficient while still being x86 c=
ompatible.

